    "Firstly, the model itself was trained on singletalker datasets but inferred with multi-talker noisy datasets, leading to a mismatch in data distribution.",
    "Secondly, our typical use of the SHAS model for audio segmentation introduced challenges, as it sometimes missed segmentations and overlooked segments containing human speech.",
    "Data shift is difficult to handle when the training dataset has not changed since last year.",
    "We focused more on handling the latter by incorporating longform decoding.",
    "The key idea is to better use context (at the text or signal level) for decoding."
